<!-- item Portugal07 --><div class="list-item box"><div class="block"><p class="title">The National Health Institute Dr. Ricardo Jorge</p><p class="owner">Health Library</p><div data-collapse><div class="moreinfo">More info</div><div><p class="desc"><b>Data owner info:</b><br>biblioteca@insa.min-saude.pt</p><P class="desc"><i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i> The Health Library of the National Health Institute Dr. Ricardo Jorge is a center of information resources to support the activities of the Institute Ricardo Jorge, and scientific  research in general. It is a library specializing in health sciences, particularly dedicated to public health in the areas of: (1) Food and nutrition, (2) Infectious diseases, (3) Human genetics, (4) Health promotion and noncommunicable disease prevention, and (5) Environmental Health and epidemiology. 
<br>Examples of projects and research areas:
<br>InsEF - National Health Survey with Physical Exam 2013-2016  <a href="http://www.insef.pt/English/Pages/Inicio.aspx">http://www.insef.pt/English/Pages/Inicio.aspx</a>
<br>HIV/ AIDS - Epidemiological situation of Infection HIV/ AIDS  <a href="http://www.insa.min-saude.pt/category/areas-de-atuacao/doencas-infeciosas/vigilancia-da-infecao-vihsida/">http://www.insa.min-saude.pt/category/areas-de-atuacao/doencas-infeciosas/vigilancia-da-infecao-vihsida/</a>
