<!-- item Scotland03 --><div class="list-item box"><div class="block"><p class="title">Pooled Sample From Population Surveys in Scotland</p><p class="owner">Scottish Government Statistics</p><div data-collapse><div class="moreinfo">More info</div><div><p class="desc"><b>Data owner info:</b><br>e-mail: statistics.enquiries@scotland.gsi.gov.uk </p><P class="desc"><i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i> The three large-scale cross sectional population surveys currently run by the Scottish Government and each published separately are: 
<br>(1) Scottish Crime and Justice Survey (SCJS), (2) Scottish Health Survey (SHeS), and (3) Scottish Household Survey (SHS). </p><p class="datalink"><i class="fa fa-laptop"></i> <b>Database:</b><br><a href="http://www.gov.scot/Topics/Statistics/About/Surveys/PooledSample2012/ExcelTables ">http://www.gov.scot/Topics/Statistics/About/Surveys/PooledSample2012/ExcelTables </a></p><p class="desc"><b>Database keywords:</b><br>Free or open access <br>Public institution<br>Institutional and quantitative (statistical) data ; Data on people’s attitudes</p><p class="keywords tohide">Scotland English Free or open access  Meta Database – quantitative Science/ Several topics</p></div></div></div></div>
<!-- item Scotland04 --><div class="list-item box"><div class="block"><p class="title">Labour Market Statistics</p><p class="owner">Labour Market Statistics</p><div data-collapse><div class="moreinfo">More info</div><div><p class="desc"><b>Data owner info:</b><br>Email: labour-market.statistics@scotland.gsi.gov.uk  
<br>Telephone:  0300 244 6773  
<br>Statistician Group Enquiries: statistics.enquiries@scotland.gsi.gov.uk</p><P class="desc"><i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i> The Labour Market Statistics cover the following topics: 
<br>(1) Headline estimates of unemployment, employment, economic inactivity, (2) Earnings, (3) Public sector employment, (4) Youth Employment, and (5) Other labour market based statistics. 

